The paper deals with the problem of computing explanations for Machine Learning models, which is a topic that falls under the broad area of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed solution involves reasoning about constraints, which is a common theme in Constraint Programming (cs.CE) and Constraint Satisfaction Problems (cs.CR). The paper also involves experimentation with datasets, which is a common theme in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Database Systems (cs.DB).
